{"sequence":19,"timestamp":"2026-04-16T05:02:04.141089112Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-ae70f96c","body":"finding_summary: The new beads health guard only runs inside `handle_propose_new_bead`; the normal bead-closing and bead-claiming flows still mutate `.beads` without any preflight validation.\nseverity: high\naffected_files:\n- src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:2998-3029\n- src/contexts/automation_runtime/success_reconciliation.rs:204-216\n- src/contexts/automation_runtime/success_reconciliation.rs:377-430\n- src/cli/project.rs:964-981\nremediation_hint: Move the health check into a shared helper and invoke it before every milestone mutation entrypoint that updates or closes bead state, not just before proposed-bead creation, so conflicted or missing `.beads/issues.jsonl` stops the operation before `br update`/`br close`/`br sync` runs.","dedup_key":"03bd5fe68d744dc157194887d137db36a6e7420bc0911cb6ea8f18412c02bc16","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260416043549","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":20,"timestamp":"2026-04-16T05:02:04.149641385Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-0335caf0","body":"finding_summary: `check_beads_health()` misidentifies ordinary `issues.jsonl` content as a merge conflict because it uses raw substring checks for `<<<<<<<`, `=======`, and `>>>>>>>`, and it also collapses every non-`NotFound` read failure into `ConflictMarkers`.\nseverity: medium\naffected_files:\n- src/adapters/br_health.rs:25-31\n- src/adapters/br_health.rs:45-46\nremediation_hint: Detect real conflict-marker lines instead of any substring match, and preserve other read failures as distinct errors so operators are not told to resolve a nonexistent merge conflict.","dedup_key":"87404d925de21cd0a169ab404f9540de0d82f52580c8875af1ff2da13e1691dd","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260416043549","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":21,"timestamp":"2026-04-16T05:02:04.158125329Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-ac145429","body":"Bug in br_health.rs:31 — the catch-all `Err(_) => return BeadsHealthStatus::ConflictMarkers` misclassifies non-NotFound I/O errors (permission denied, disk errors) as conflict markers. The downstream error message in service.rs:3004 then tells the operator to \"resolve the conflict\" when the real problem is unreadable file state. Fix: either add a new `BeadsHealthStatus::IoError` variant, or fall through to `BrUnavailable` which at least doesn't produce an actively wrong diagnosis. The fail-safe blocking behavior is correct, only the reported reason is wrong.","dedup_key":"ac28af9a82118c6a3305229986e9c98b438e6147aa786b64cd1c1189717be5cc","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"claude","model_id":"claude-opus-4-6-max","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260416043549","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
